RACE.RACE_TEXT: KEENELAND RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 69000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. Claiming Price $150,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOOTPRINT lacked speed in the two path, launched a rally in the five path entering the far turn, progressed quickly and swept past the leader while tucking to the three path at the quarter pole and drew clear. TIS CHARMING laid off of the pace in the three path, gained inside of rivals into the far turn, attempted a two wide bid for the lead along with an outer rival approaching the quarter pole, but was quickly outkicked by that one at that marker, gained place entering the lane and was second best. TOWN HALL set the pace with a clear margin, but was overhauled with a quarter mile to go, weakened yet lasted safely for show. TITLE CONTENDER laid off of the pace in the four path, but was outmoved by rivals on either side around the far turn and failed to threaten. STONE HARBOR chased in the two path, weakened between horses with five sixteenths to go and was eased up through the lane. T B TWELVE ALWAYS trailed along the inside, was done into the far turn, eased and jogged home. MIDNITE LUMBERJACK tracked in the two to three path, but weakened between horses entering the far turn and was eased thereafter.

MISINTENTION laid off of the pace in the three path, then along the inside around the far turn and failed to factor. PERCEPTIVE stalked in the four path, but yielded position outside of rivals with five furlongs to go, failed to respond to urging approaching the far turn and faded.
